translated_poem:
Ye, who seeks safe repose in
life, through numerous tasks;
to whom, sighted of the world’s benefits,
thy reign is enclosed;
 bestow, if desired so, to Confusion
fresh honours and blind sacrifices;
for that same punishment of old sins,
it is God’s will that all things take the path of righteousness
 However, one who blamed chance,
did not suffer from this form of punishment, one whom only believes that chance is all that is in this World.
 The grand experience is also the great evil;
what is to God fair and pure,
is also unjust and vast to mankind.
